         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">In honour</supplied> of Curnius. To Lucius Volusius Bassus Cerealis, of senatorial and consular status, curator of his own city, 
               for which, along with other public works that he renewed by his industry and tremendous effort, he restored the basilica Ulpia, with its public place, to a better appearance using public money; offering their gratitude, the Lepcitanians, publicly.</p></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Curnius! A Lucius Volusius Bassus Cerealis, uomo chiarissimo
               e consolare, curatore della propria repubblica, per il fatto
               che, tra le altre opere che rinnovò con la sua operosità e con
               il più grande sforzo, restituì – con pubblica spesa – un aspetto
               migliore alla Basilica Ulpia insieme con . . .(?), in segno di riconoscimento
               i Leptitani, a spese pubbliche.</p></div> 
         <div type="translation" source="#lsa" xml:lang="en">
            <p>(Statue of) Curnius. To Lucius Volusius Bassus Caerealis, of clarissimus and consular rank, curator of his home city; 
               for, among other works that he renovated with industry and the greatest labour, he restored the Ulpian basilica with . . . 
               to a better appearance, at public expense. Offering thanks, the people of Lepcis (<foreign xml:lang="la">Lepcitani</foreign>) [set this up] from public funds. </p>
         </div>
